<p>This <strong>Technology Update Notification</strong> (TUN) is being published to inform you of changes or additions to Lumen Technologyâ€™s network architecture, hardware, software or device configuration. This TUN is a dated document and reflects changes to the architecture, hardware, software, or device configuration at this moment in time. As such, subsequent policy updates may be issued at a later date that could override this document.</p>

<h1 id="purpose">Purpose</h1>
<p>This <strong>Technology Update Notification</strong> advises the respective groups of the proposed changes to the currently approved configurations in <strong>Lumenâ€™s</strong> network. A <strong>TUN</strong> is accompanied by WIKI documents that have been updated with information about new deployment standards and general configuration templates. A <strong>TUN</strong> announces that the architecture design work has been completed, with new architectures documented and approved by the architecture team. This <strong>TUN</strong> can be used as a notification to other teams and a handoff for further development.</p>

<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"><i class="fa fa-warning"></i> <b>Important:</b> <strong>A TUN does not approve technologies or configuration changes, for use in the production network.</strong></div>

<h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>
<p>The <a href="http://wiki.level3.com/wiki/Network_Architecture_and_Design_-_Third_Party_Optics">Third Party Optics</a>  wiki describes the approved certification and use of Champion One optics in the various IP/Data Routing, Switching and NID platforms deployed within the affiliate CenturyLink Networks. To date Champion One Optics have been Tested and Certified for use in the <strong>Metro 2.0/ 3.0, AS209, ILEC Metro, AS3549 (MPLS) and AS 3356 (Internet )</strong> networks.</p>

